        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In the assemble method of the Zend_Controller_Router_Rewrite, if the $reset parameter is set to true, but the $name parameter is set to null, the current route is used.  I propose that instead, if $name is null and $reset is true, then $name should be set to 'default', but if $reset is false then it should instead be set to the current route.\n\nThe current code for the relevant block is as follows:\n{code:title=Zend\/Controller\/Router\/Rewrite.php}\n\/\/ ...\n    public function assemble($userParams, $name = null, $reset = false, $encode = true)\n    {\n        if ($name == null) {\n            try {\n                $name = $this->getCurrentRouteName();\n            } catch (Zend_Controller_Router_Exception $e) {\n                $name = 'default';\n            }\n        }\n\/\/ ...\n{code}\n\nMy proposed change:\n{code:title=Zend\/Controller\/Router\/Rewrite.php}\n\/\/ ...\n    public function assemble($userParams, $name = null, $reset = false, $encode = true)\n    {\n        if ($name == null) {\n            if($reset) {\n                $name = 'default';\n            } else {\n                try {\n                    $name = $this->getCurrentRouteName();\n                } catch (Zend_Controller_Router_Exception $e) {\n                    $name = 'default';\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\/\/ ...\n{code}\n\nThis (in my mind) would be more consistent with the meaning and purpose of the $reset parameter."
        },
